(9, 'A Comprehensive Guide to UI UX Design', '2022-06-28 14:55:58', 'When it comes to web and app development; UI and UX can be two of the most confusing terms, especially for beginners. Since both user interface (UI) and user experience (UX) are usually mentioned together (as UI/UX), people tend to think that the term is referring to the same thing. \r\n\r\nHowever, user interface and user experience are like two different sides of the same coin. Both are connected in the sense that they make up a website, but differ when it comes to their characteristics. \r\n\r\nToday, we will be looking at what differentiates both. Read down for user experience and user interface design guidelines. \r\n\r\nWhat’s the Difference Between UI and UX? \r\nAccording to Rahul Varshney, co-creator of Foster.fm: “User Experience (UX) and User Interface (UI) are some of the most confused and misused terms in our field. A UI without UX is like a painter slapping paint onto canvas without thought; while UX without UI is like the frame of a sculpture with no paper match on it. A great product experience starts with UX followed by UI. Both are essential for the product’s success.” \r\n\r\nuser-interface-design-guidelines\r\n\r\nA user experience designer aims to understand the customers journey, which includes understanding customers, target audience, aspects of branding, conducting user testing, defining user flow etc. \r\n\r\nWhereas the role of a user interface designer is to focus on the logos, design, typography, color theme, and the visual design of a website. \r\n\r\nRead down below for more clarity.\r\n\r\nRecommended: IMPORTANT STEPS IN A USER CENTERED PRODUCT DESIGN PROCESS\r\n\r\nWhat is User interface design?\r\nUI or User Interface design development is the process of improving user’s interaction with a website or application, making it as easy to use and effective as possible. User interface development focuses primarily on the look and design of the websites and web applications \r\n\r\nThe elements of a website such as menus, icons, buttons and pages and all other visual elements contribute to the user UI of that website. In short, the main goal of a UI developer is to create a convenient interface, that fulfill the user’s needs. \r\n\r\nuser-interface-design-guidelines \r\n\r\n“Design is not just what it looks like and feels like. Design is how it works” –SteveJobs \r\n\r\nEssential properties of well-designed UI \r\nYou can find a lot of information on the internet regarding different design patterns and techniques that can be used to craft websites and apps.\r\n\r\nFollowing guidelines from experts can be very helpful in creating  a good user-interface – but what exactly does a good UI design refer to? Let’s have a look at some of the main principles of an effective user-interface. \r\n\r\nUI-designer\r\n \r\n\r\n1. Clarity \r\nWhere do I find the main menu? If you’ve ever asked this question to yourself upon visiting a website, you’ve probably had to deal with a user interface that was poorly designed. \r\n\r\nIf people don’t understand how your website works or how to find the particular product/service they are looking for, they are likely to get frustrated and switch to another website that provides a better user-interface. \r\n\r\nAn ideal website design is the one that allows users to navigate easily and smoothly. The elements of the website I.e., icons, menus, search bars, buttons, etc. should be laid out neatly, so they don’t cause any user disruption. The quicker the visitor can get his task done on your website, the happier he is going to be with your service. \r\n\r\n2. Familiarity \r\nA lot of designer’s design with the goal of making the interface of the website/app ‘intuitive.’ But what exactly is an intuitive design? As far as web/app design is concerned, an intuitive design is the one that can be comprehended and understood instinctively.\r\n\r\nSo, how do you make your website design intuitive? By making it familiar! \r\n\r\nIn simple words, when a user opens your website, he/she should not require guidance on what to do next. For this, it is important that you integrate elements that are familiar to your users. \r\n\r\nRecommended: UI VS UX DESIGN – A QUICK COMPARISON\r\n\r\n3. Attractiveness \r\nAn attractive user-interface is more important than what most people think. Think about it yourself, would you rather enjoy surfing a website that’s plain and boring, or the one that’s enjoyable and appealing to the eye? Probably the second.  \r\n\r\nTrue, this might not be a 100% necessary thing when it comes to UX development, but it can make a lot of difference to the way your customers perceive your brand.\r\n\r\nThis does not mean one should load their website with superfluous eye-candy, but to merely polish their interface to make the experience remember able for the visitor. \r\n\r\n4. Maintainability \r\nA good user experience design should offer the flexibility of conveniently making changes to the design when needed, without causing a conflict of interest. \r\n\r\nFor instance, if you need to make alternations to the software, or include an additional feature, the process should be straightforward and easy. It should not compromise other features or cause flaws in the overall design itself. \r\n\r\nYou might also want to read: THE IMPORTANCE OF USER INTERFACE DESIGN IN MOBILE APPLICATIONS\r\n\r\nWhat is User experience design?\r\nUX or User Experience development is the process of making a website more engaging, interactive and useful. In simple words, it is the procedure of developing and improving the quality of experience of users when they visit a website or application. \r\n\r\nUnlike UI development, UX development does not focus on the visuals; instead, it aims to improve the overall feel of the experience. It focuses primarily on wireframing a website, and structuring all its elements and components appropriately to create the user flow. \r\n\r\nuser-interface-design-guidelines \r\nVital Elements of Good User Experience \r\nAccording to stats, more than 65% of people prefer to read a UX-optimized site over a plain webpage. The UX design is one of the main factors that sets your website apart from the competitors. Let’s have a look at some of the essential elements of a good user-interface. \r\n\r\nUX-designer\r\n \r\n\r\n1. Accessibility \r\nAn effective website is the one that is accessible to everyone including the elderly, blind and disabled. There are a lot of features that can make your website user-friendly for disabled and blind people.\r\n\r\nFor example, you can include a text-to-speech feature for people who can’t see the content of your website. \r\n\r\n2. Mobile Compatibility \r\nThe number of mobile users around the globe is constantly increasing. Nowadays, users prefer to access websites through their phones rather than laptops. Hence, mobile optimization holds a lot of importance for user experience. \r\n\r\nThe mobile app design of your website should be clean and understandable, and should have a quick page load-time. \r\n\r\n3. Product Discovery \r\nAccording to research conducted by Klevu, there are usability and accessibility issues with the search experience on 80% of UK ecommerce websites. A lot of businesses are losing revenue due to poor product discovery.  \r\n\r\nIf users can’t find the product they are looking for; they are not going to purchase it. It’s as simple as that. The products and content on your website should be easily discoverable for a good overall user experience design. \r\n\r\n4. Load Time\r\nNothing is more annoying than a website that takes a lot of time to load. In fact, slow page load time is one of the main reasons for visitors to abandon a website. Your website should take 4-5 seconds to load, at most.  \r\n\r\nMoreover, load time can also affect your search engine rankings. A specific algorithm is used by Google to determine the ranking of a website, and the page load speed is one of the factors analyzed. \r\n\r\nTherefore, you might want to put  in all the effort it takes into reducing the load time of your website.', ''),
(10, 'Top 5 Loopholes to Avoid for your ECommerce Website', '2022-06-28 14:57:50', 'According to stats, there are more than 24 million ecommerce websites present on the internet, and more are being created every day. However, not all of these websites are successful. \r\n\r\nThere are a lot of factors that need to be considered in order to build an effective website. At times, even the smallest ecommerce mistake can cause bigger problems in the long-run. However, with proper planning and execution, these mistakes can be avoided. \r\n\r\nToday, we will be looking at some of the common ecommerce mistakes to avoid. \r\n\r\nTop 5 ecommerce website development mistakes to avoid\r\nRead down below to find out more. \r\n\r\n1. Choosing the wrong eCommerce platform\r\nThe very first ecommerce website development mistake on the list is the most popular and basic one; not choosing the right ecommerce platform. \r\n\r\nA recent study by Forrester shows that most of the ecommerce businesses are not happy with their current ecommerce platform and are hence looking to migrate. \r\n\r\nEvery ecommerce business wants to choose an ecommerce web solution that is robust, scalable, and supports multiple business models. However, a lot of businesses succumb to deceptive sale tactics used by ecommerce solution vendors. \r\n\r\nWhy is it important to choose the right solution?\r\nNot choosing the right platform can lead to several issues such as revenue loss, security issues, less conversions, bad customer experience, and much more. Also, shifting your platform to a different one later one requires a lot of extra time, cost and effort.  \r\n\r\nMake a list of the ecommerce website features your business requires according to your business model, and the type of design you want for your website. Both of which will ultimately help you choose the right ecommerce platform based on your ecommerce model.  \r\n\r\nSome of the important factors to consider while choosing an ecommerce platform are: \r\n\r\nType of products you will be offering \r\nBudget constraints and business scalability \r\nType of tools you would need for website development \r\nMobile and SEO friendliness of the website\r\n2. Ignoring the importance of SEO optimization\r\nA lot of online businesses don’t realize the importance of search engine optimization, until they dig into the reasons for their website not receiving traffic. A website that is not SEO optimized is likely to become obsolete in no time.  However, this common ecommerce mistake can be avoided easily.  \r\n\r\nOn-site SEO is important because it allows your website to appear in Search Engine Results Page (SERP) features. Also, customers are more likely to click on the websites that appear on the first page of Google search results.  \r\n\r\nWhy is SEO important?\r\nAccording to Backlinko,“The number one result in Google’s organic search results has an average CTR of 31.7 percent. The number one organic result is 10 times more likely to receive a click compared to a page in number 10 spot. . . On average, moving up one spot in the search results will increase CTR by 30.8 percent.”  \r\n\r\nThe only way you can make your website climb up in the search rankings is if you are making proper use of Seo strategies. Therefore, search engine optimization should be on your priority list when it comes to ecommerce mistakes to avoid.\r\n\r\nHere are some ways to rank your e-commerce website: \r\n\r\nResearch and target the right keywords for your service \r\nMake use of catchy title, headings, and meta descriptions \r\nCheck the loading speed of your website  \r\nCreate an attractive ecommerce website design \r\nMake sure your website structure is usable \r\nAnalyze your competitors and look at the SEO strategies that are helping them rank.\r\n3. Poor filter options and difficult navigation \r\nPoor filter options and difficult navigation are two of the most popular technical issues in e-commerce websites. These small avoidable mistakes made by ecommerce companies leads to higher bounce rates and cart abandonment. \r\n\r\nAccording to research conducted by Klevu, there are usability and accessibility issues with the search experience on 80% of UK ecommerce websites. \r\n\r\nHow can this mistake be avoided?\r\nEcommerce websites that are easy to navigate and provide search options for quick product search are always preferred by customers over the ones that are difficult to navigate.  \r\n\r\nThink about this yourself, would you rather check out a website that is easy to use or the one that would take you a lot of time to figure out. \r\n\r\nUser interface is extremely important for good customer experience. Therefore, it is important that you ask the ecommerce website development company you’ve hired to keep the interface clean, simple, and usable. Also, the more filter options you include; the better. \r\n\r\nA few ecommerce website features that can help are: \r\n\r\nA Call to Action (CTA) button \r\nA search bar on all pages \r\nFilter options according to product name, brand, price range etc. \r\nDrop down menus \r\n4. Complicated checkout process\r\nHave you ever visited a website and abandoned it later on because the checkout process is too complicated? Frustrating, isn’t it? Surprisingly, this is also one of the most common errors you see with eCommerce websites. \r\n\r\nNot only does this result in the loss of a potential customer, but that customer is also likely to warn other people about not wasting time on the website.\r\n\r\nHow to provide a convenient checkout process?\r\n\r\nA convenient checkout process is one the best characteristics of good ecommerce website. Therefore, try to make your websites checkout process as short and easy as possible.  \r\n\r\nFurthermore, customers will also avoid purchasing from your website if you don’t offer their choice of payment. Hence, you should include as many payment methods as possible to further improve customer satisfaction.  \r\n\r\nSome of the most popular payment methods include: \r\n\r\nCredit/debit card payment \r\nPayPal, WeChat Pay, AliPay, Union pay etc \r\nMasterpass, Visa Checkout  \r\nPre-paid-card, gift card \r\nCash on delivery \r\nYou might also want to read: Quick guide to ecommerce website development\r\n\r\n5. Doing everything yourself\r\nThis a pitfall faced by a lot of ecommerce business out there. Yes, building your own ecommerce website yourself sounds like a nice idea if you’ve got the perfect design in your mind. But, do you think it would work perfectly in the end? \r\n\r\nWhy should I hire a professional ecommerce website development company?\r\nIf you’re not someone who is experienced in ecommerce website development, then it’s best for you to leave the website design and development at the hand of professionals.\r\n\r\nEspecially if you are a start-up and don’t have the budget to hire in-house developers. Why? Because building an ecommerce is a complicated and lengthy process. Also, it requires a lot of tools and coding knowledge that takes years for ecommerce website developers to learn. \r\n\r\nFor the best results, you can hire professional ecommerce developers for reliable ecommerce website development services. Meanwhile, you can focus on scalability plans and strategies to expand your business in the future. ', ''),
(11, 'Benefits of automation in healthcare industry', '2022-06-28 15:03:29', 'The Covid-19 pandemic has impacted some nations so adversely that their healthcare systems have reached the point of exhaustion. In fact, the pandemic has been an eye-opener, forcing leaders and healthcare providers to focus on the dire need for automation in the healthcare sector to lessen the burden on the industry as a whole.\r\n\r\nAutomation is the future of healthcare, without it, the whole system is bound to crumble. Today, we are going to be talking about the benefits of automation in the healthcare industry, and why we heavily rely on it nowadays. Read down below to find out all about it.\r\n\r\nWhat benefits does automation provide for healthcare services?\r\nAccording to Deloitte, in 2021, the health tech industry is expected to hit $280 billion with a CAGR of 15.9% between 2016-2021. Curious to know how technology helps healthcare services? Let’s see.\r\n\r\n1. Quicker data retrieval \r\nData retrieval holds critical importance in the medical world. Retrieval and analysis of data allow doctors and physicians instant access to the electronic health records of patients. The different functions of data retrieval and analysis directly impact different aspects of health care including billing procedures and medical diagnosis.\r\n\r\nThough data retrieval used to be a time-consuming task a few years back, electronic health record (EHR) machines now allow real-time data retrieval effectively, within minutes. This has not only helped make the whole data extraction process easier but has also improved patient care. \r\n\r\n2. Improved ordering\r\nManual ordering process can take a lot of time and effort. Thanks to the EHR machine, it is possible to complete orders only with a few clicks. It is expected that the efficiency in the ordering process will increase further in the coming years with the help of predictive artificial intelligence and machine learning technologies.\r\n\r\n3. Faster billing\r\nBilling in healthcare used to be another hectic task before the advent of smart machines. But now, healthcare institutions can quickly generate bills through AI machines. This reduces the wait time for patients, improves patient care, and increases customer satisfaction.\r\n\r\nHow does healthcare automation help patients?\r\nThe global EHR/EMR market is expected to reach $38 billion by 2025. Automation provides countless benefits for patients. Some of them include:\r\n\r\n1. Early disease detection\r\nThere are hundreds of benefits of early disease detection in patients. Not only does it allow doctors and physicians to get started with the treatment early, but it can also be a life-saver most of the time. Thanks to technologies like AI and machine learning, it is now possible to diagnose illnesses and diseases within days and even minutes.\r\n\r\nMoreover, advanced technology can even detect whether a patient is affected by a particular disease even before its symptoms appear. For example, early-stage lung cancer can be detected through neural networks. The earlier the disease is detected, the quicker it can get treated, and catching cancer at its first stage can significantly increase a patient’s survival rate as compared to diagnosing in its last stages.\r\n\r\n2. Precision and speed in medical diagnosis\r\nTime is a critical aspect when it comes to healthcare. If a disease is not diagnosed on time, there are more chances that it becomes fatal quickly. However, a speedy diagnosis can  save a patient’s life. At times, medical practitioners can make serious mistakes and blunders trying to diagnose a patient’s illness. On the other hand, the chances of errors are dramatically reduced with automated systems in healthcare.\r\n\r\nOther than this, through healthcare automation solutions, it is also possible to detect patient deviation from prescribed health plans, allowing doctors to take care of the situation in real-time. Also, automation has helped make it easier and more convenient for patients to buy drugs from automated dispensing machines in hospitals, rather than having to wait in long queues.\r\n\r\n4. Improved patient management and participation\r\nTele health and telemedicine mobile apps have made it much easier for patients to get quality healthcare and medical attention on time. In fact, mobile apps have even made it possible for people living in remote locations to get the medical care they need without having to visit the hospital.\r\n\r\nThe benefits of mobile apps in the healthcare industry include faster access to healthcare, better communication and collaboration between patients and doctors, improved medication adherence, an easier appointment booking process, and much more.\r\n\r\n5. Minimal errors\r\nEven the slightest possible error in health care provision can result in a huge problem later on. At times, doctors and physicians tend to make errors due to inattentiveness and fatigue. However, automated machines don’t suffer from the weakness that humans do, and hence the chances of errors are also very less. This means precise results, quicker diagnosis, and improved quality of healthcare.\r\n\r\n6. Improved healthcare quality\r\nThe biggest all-encompassing benefit of robotic process automation in the medical industry is that it promotes superior quality healthcare. Through quicker diagnosis, reduced error occurrences, and more time for healthcare providers to focus on patient-centric activities, the effectiveness of healthcare has more than doubled over the past few years.\r\n\r\nMoreover, since a lot of processes in healthcare have been automated, the excessive burden on healthcare providers reduced dramatically, allowing them to pay attention to more patients simultaneously.\r\n\r\n7. Better communication \r\nAccording to Jackson healthcare, 64% Americans prefer to communicate with their doctors via video tele health.\r\n\r\nEnhanced communication is another major benefit that automation in healthcare has provided. It is now possible for doctors and patients to stay in contact with one another 24/7 without having to visit the hospital every day. \r\n\r\nMoreover, with the help of daily reminders and notifications, the number of missed appointments and meetings have also reduced for patients. Appointment booking, cancellations, and rescheduling can also be done much quicker and conveniently. This helps streamline the whole system and allows patients to get care at the right time.', ''),
(12, 'How to Effectively Market Your Healthcare Software Online?', '2022-06-28 15:05:16', 'Business promotion through social media is one of the best ways of increasing brand awareness and we have many examples to back this up. The same can be applied to healthcare software promotion. Today we’ll learn how marketing healthcare software can be beneficial for business growth and enhance your digital presence.\r\n\r\nHow Social Media Enhances Healthcare Software Marketing?\r\nhealthcare-software-marketing-facebook\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe days of word-of-mouth referral systems have become old, obsolete, and inefficient when it comes to marketing. In this digital age, most companies are going for personalized software. This is why custom software development for the healthcare sector has become quite investible.\r\n\r\nThis option becomes increasingly beneficial when you realize that social media not only assists healthcare software marketing efforts but also helps you set up an environment for your customers to converge to. The type of social media campaign that you will set up for your business after the healthcare software development process is complete, will ensure the type of response you will get from your audience. \r\n\r\nChoosing software for your healthcare business is just the first part of your business progression. Crucial healthcare software marketing aspects such as website review score, app reviews, user-friendliness, and customer interaction will define how users perceive your software.\r\n\r\nAlso Read: Benefits of automation in healthcare industry\r\n\r\nHow to Strengthen my Healthcare Software’s Online presence?\r\nSocial media marketing is all about consistency. The marketing strategies must include frequent content postings, so the algorithms and the visitors know that your business is active. Now, a well-developed healthcare software can sell itself but in reality, it is just a product. The face of your business are your website and social media handles. The marketing strategy will define your business and the healthcare software development company’s online perception.\r\n\r\nHere’s how to sell healthcare software?\r\n1)  Choose Suitable Platforms for your Healthcare Software Marketing Efforts\r\nHealthcare businesses must understand that not every social media platform is suitable for businesses. Although there are some trending apps like TikTok or Snapchat for business promotion but not everyone can benefit from them. \r\n\r\nMoreover, when it comes to healthcare software marketing, you should largely focus on platforms that can effectively promote your business online. Social media apps like Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and LinkedIn are more apt for healthcare-related marketing strategies.\r\n\r\n2)   Study the Competitors Thoroughly\r\nEven in the medical business, it is best practice to keep an eye on your competitors marketing initiatives. Before you build your social media marketing strategy, analyze how your competition is doing it. Try to figure out what strategies are working for them and which ones are causing their Binge Google search engine rankings to fall.\r\n\r\nAfter thoroughly studying your competitor’s strategy to increase awareness for their healthcare software, you will also be able to devise a comprehensive campaign that best fits your company’s requirements, goals, and objectives.\r\n\r\nUseful tips: take note of their popular posts, content that makes their page different, and how they are interacting with visitors. Also, try to see whether they are doing extra activities like holding webinars on LinkedIn or online conferences related to specific topics. All of this contributes to how they attract visitors to their page, eventually leading them to their website or software.\r\n\r\n3)   Create Engaging Content for your Healthcare Software Marketing Campaigns\r\nWhenever you visit a page on Facebook, there is a high tendency that you are judging the page/company by the type of content it is displaying. Low-quality images and written content that hardly contain any information are exactly what you have to avoid. Since the main objective of these healthcare software marketing efforts, you will have to create plenty of informational content. \r\n\r\nTalk about how your software product can do better, pull up infographics, and even hold polls to increase audience interaction. Try ‘Did You Know?’ posts as well!\r\n\r\nRead More: SQUID GAME & MARKETING: A PERFECT DUO\r\n\r\n4)   Don’t Be Afraid Of Reviews!\r\nWhether you are the owner of an on-demand healthcare mobile app, or a custom healthcare software development company, one thing is evident: you need to be in the good books when it comes to online ratings & reviews. It is great customer service if you provide your clients with a chance to drop reviews. Let them talk about what they think about your healthcare software or your business. \r\n\r\nRemember: Even negative reviews & comments are an opportunity for improvement. Reviews only work best if you constantly go through them and see what customers are saying about you.\r\n\r\nUltimately, you are setting up a base of confidence for your new visitors and customers who are looking for medical services. Bad reviews would not scare them away if they also know how you have improved. This will tell them how you are constantly working to improve your services.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\nIf you are doing your online marketing the right way, chances are that your healthcare web and mobile app development efforts will not go in vain. \r\n\r\nIt is always good to remember that while developers may provide a great UI/UX design, how you market your product afterward will be the deciding factor. Whether it is a mobile app or website, make sure you choose a platform that aligns exactly with your company goals and marketing objectives. ', '');

